Q01: Interest: Is the app interesting to use? Does it use any strategies to increase engagement by  presenting its content in an interesting way?
Q02: Interactivity: Does it allow user input, provide feedback, contain prompts (reminders, sharing  options, notifications, etc.)? Note: these functions need to be customisable and not  overwhelming in order to be perfect.
Q03: Target group: Is the app content (visual information, language, design) appropriate?
Q04: Performance: How accurately/fast do the app features (functions) and components  (buttons/menus) work?
Q05: Ease of use: How easy is it to learn how to use the app; how clear are the menu labels/icons and  instructions?
Q06: Gestural design: Are interactions (taps/swipes/pinches/scrolls) consistent and intuitive across  all components/screens?
Q07: Layout: Is arrangement and size of buttons/icons/menus/content on the screen appropriate or  zoomable if needed?
Q08: Graphics: How high is the quality/resolution of graphics used for buttons/icons/menus/content?
Q09: Visual appeal: How good does the app look?
Q10: Quality of information: Is the app content correct, well written, and relevant to the goal/topic of the app?
Q11: Quantity of information: Is the extent of coverage within the scope of the app; and comprehensive but concise?
Q12: Visual information: Is the visual explanation of concepts – through/graphs/images/models, etc.  – clear, logical, and correct?
Q13: Would you recommend this app to people who might benefit from it?
Q14: How many times do you think you would use this app in the next 12 months if it was relevant to you?
Q15: Would you pay for this app?
Q16: What is your overall star rating of the app?
